AWKA – The police in Anambra state has successfully quelled attacks on Neni and Aguata police divisional headquarters killing three out of four hoodlums who launched the attacks. The police commissioner CP Echeng Eworo Echeng who made this public on Monday assured Anambra citizens that the command will continue to sustain the tempo of crime fighting in the state, noting that operatives will not relent against the onslaught on violent crimes. The police commissioner’s statement which was released to journalists in Awka on Monday by the Police Public Relations Officer DSP Ikenga Tochukwu noted that police operatives successfully repelled an attack in the late hours of Sunday on Aguata and Neni Divisional Headquarters. Just In: Assailants Kill Housewife, Pound Her Toddlers In Kano Attempted Murder: Police Arraign Fani-Kayode’s Estranged… The statement has it that operatives demobilized four of the armed hoodlums and recover 17pcs of 7.62mm live ammunition for Ak 47rifle, 107 pics of expended 7.62mm ammunition for Ak47 rifle, 7 pics of expended cartridges for pump action, 10 pics of expended 7.62mm long for Lar rifle, one big hammer, 3 phones and a wallet containing ID’s and some ATM cards. It also said that preliminary information revealed that one out of three of the demobilized miscreants, now late Mr Onyebuchi Okoye “M” 34years, who led the attack on Aguata Divisional headquarters was arrested earlier on 4th November, 2021 with a revolver pistol and six 9mm ammunition by Police Operatives. The statement said he was charged to court for conspiracy to commit felony and unlawful possession of firearms under section 495 of the criminal code and on 21/01/2022 was granted bail by the Court. Also at Neni division, the gunmen fled the scene due to the superior fire of the police operatives on duty. Both stations were  intact and no arm was lost as contained in the PPRO’s report.